Remdar v1.0 was in Da`Kor, and looted Emarr’s first Ethereal Mist Breastplate on one of the VERY early PoF runs.  At that moment, all other clerics had died or camped and the group was being overrun, he was the last potential user of the piece still alive to get it.  Hard as it may be for someone who didn’t experience the brutality that was a Fear break after that notorious zone upgrade to imagine, it was absolute and utter chaos, and the fact that anyone at all was able to make use of the item was astonishing given the circumstances.  That scenario, however, wasn’t enough to subdue an individual’s rage at not being able to loot the item, even though all logic available for that split second decision said it was the right thing to do.  The resulting acts of rage on Justicia’s part were anything but passive.  While I’d never expect any of my crew to forgive her, Justi apologized to me in my goodbye thread earnestly, and I’ve accepted that and moved on.<br>
<br>
Zolen was in our guild for a time and did everything he could to benefit others, including passing on drops he could’ve used to see others improve themselves.  Increasingly towards the end of his days with us, he was prone to large mood swings that left most of the guild wondering which side of him we’d be seeing that day, or even that hour, which made a lot of us sad, including myself (I was one of his sponsors into the guild).  He took issue with some guild policies and chose to direct his hate primarily at me while leaving the guild.  He was at best 54th level at the time, and probably not even that, as he quit right around the time we were first discovering Old Sebilis.  Not to demean his contributions, but he was no where near “main tank” as you suggest based on your hearsay.  He has since pissed off many people and made friends with many more.<br>
<br>
Kanya touched on Tzzird’s character, there’s not really much else to say.  She’s a dear friend who does her best to be objective on this board despite all baiting to do otherwise.  You’re the only person I know who has any issue with Tzzird that I’m aware of.  I’ve met him in RL, and count him as a friend.  I guess you found a button to push that no one else has.<br>
<br>
Kuzic is as loyal as a pit bull to the people he loves, and anyone who’s played with him should count themselves fortunate.<br>
<br>
Ogmuk is a big-hearted individual who looks out for his friends.  The game wore on him earlier than most, and he withdrew from it shortly after Kunark opened.  <br>
<br>
Da`Kor has been gone from EQ for nearly seven months.  Put another way, Da`Kor has been gone from EQ for nearly ONE FOURTH of the game’s commercial existence.  We must’ve been one hell of an act for people to still be talking so fervently about us so long after the show left town.<br>
<br>
The point?  You embellish your references beyond any grain of truth, you lean on associations with Ogmuk for leverage when he’s not had an active role in guild management for nearly two years, and you globally defame an entire guild for personal disagreements with a couple people.  Worse yet, you target us directly as though those specific members of ours were the only people you ever had a problem with on this server.<br>
<br>
You are right about one thing: Remdar cast offensively through walls against specters in the caves.  Where you err is in blaming and blasting an entire guild that over time had more than 80 unique people go through it’s halls as members based on your opinions regarding those actions that fuel your hatred.  Nothing is as black and white as you make this or any other issue out to be, and your hate-filled spew is ten times more evil than any perceived wrong you were on the end of while controlling your avatar in a game.  You claim implicitly to follow tenets of zen and monk societies.  These groups preach forgiveness and tolerance, not hatred-filled witch hunts.  You’re about as far away from that ideology as you could possibly be. <br>
